The getWebArtifactEdit() method in my previous comment is this:

    private WebArtifactEdit getWebArtifactEdit() {
        IVirtualComponent webComponent = getWebComponent(_project);
        assert webComponent != null : "null web component"; //$NON-NLS-1$
        WebArtifactEdit model  =
WebArtifactEdit.getWebArtifactEditForWrite(webComponent);                        
        return model;        
    }

We're not doing anything tricky to extend the edit model, just wrapping it in an
API that is useful for our needs.

